{{!--
    Series navigation dispatcher (articles plan Tier 2.5).

    One {{#has}} branch per series. Each renders the shared series-strip when the
    current post carries that series's internal tag (`#series-<slug>`). Internal
    tags ARE present on the post in theme context (they even leak as card pills —
    see Tier 2.1), so {{#has tag="hash-series-..."}} matches them.

    Empty until the first series exists — renders nothing, zero visual impact.

    CONTRACT (kept in sync by the `developassion-publish` skill + src/data/series.json):
      * Membership + order come from the `#series-<slug>` internal tag applied to
        posts in Ghost; order = publish date. Adding a post to an EXISTING series
        needs ONLY the tag — no edit here, the strip fetches members dynamically.
      * Creating a NEW series adds ONE branch below, between the INSERT markers.
        Keep the markers intact and one blank line between branches.

    currentId=id passes the viewed post's id so the strip can mark "You're here".
--}}
